This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new class of Contextual Recurrent Neural Networks for Recommendation (CRNNs) that can take into account contextual information for recommendation. It also uses Deep Learning models for user representation. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with recommendation systems that are a type of information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing in the form of user-item interactions. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new approach for recommendation using AI techniques. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper deals with sequence modeling, which is a common technique in computer vision and pattern recognition.
